# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Childbooks — environment templates have moved.
#
# The app is now split into a frontend + a backend, each with its own template:
#
#   • Backend secrets (OpenAI / Gemini / Lulu keys, asset hosting):
#       functions/.env.example          → copy to functions/.env.local
#
#   • Frontend public config (NEXT_PUBLIC_*, no secrets):
#       books-frontend/.env.example     → copy to books-frontend/.env.local
#
# There is no longer a single root env file: secrets live ONLY in the backend.
# See books-frontend/README.md for the full setup, and for where (not) to put a
# Firebase service-account key.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
